Apple will maintain its entry-level pricing for the standard iPhone 17 this year, but the iPhone 17 Pro and iPhone 17 Pro Max are set to get price hikes, albeit with a minimum storage boost for the iPhone 17 Pro model, according to <a href="https://www.trendforce.com/presscenter/news/20250904-12700.html">TrendForce</a>.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/07/iPhone-17-Pro-Iridescent-Feature-2.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1011128" /><br/>
The market research company expects the regular iPhone 17 model to have the same &#36;799 starting price and 128GB base storage as last year's iPhone 16, while both the iPhone 17 Pro and iPhone 17 Pro Max will come with 256GB base storage options and increases of &#36;50-&#36;100 per comparable capacity. The full iPhone 17 lineup pricing could break down like so:<br/>
